    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <head>No. 48.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Partridge</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 21,
                                1871</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your dispatch No. 13, of the
                            23d ultimo, communicating the agreeable intelligence of the appointment
                            by the princess regent of Brazil, in the name of the Emperor, of Baron
                            de Itajubá to be a member of the Tribunal of Arbitration under Article
                            of the <pb facs="0169" n="73" xml:id="pg_73"/> Treaty of Washington, I
                            have to express to you the sincere gratification afforded to the
                            President by the selection of so eminent and learned a gentleman.</p>
                <p>I am. &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
